import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['price'], label='S&P 500 Price', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.title('What is the trend of S&P 500 prices over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['price'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='S&P 500 Prices')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of S&P 500 prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.to_period('M')
    data['monthly_return'] = data['price'].pct_change()
    monthly_avg_return = data.groupby('month')['monthly_return'].mean()

    ax = monthly_avg_return.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(15, 7), color='blue', legend=True)
    avg_line = monthly_avg_return.mean()
    plt.axhline(y=avg_line, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_line:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average monthly return of S&P 500?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('Average Monthly Return')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    std_dev = data['price'].std()
    data['upper_band'] = data['price'] + std_dev
    data['lower_band'] = data['price'] - std_dev
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['price'], label='S&P 500 Price', color='blue')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['upper_band'], label=f'+1 Std Dev ({std_dev:.2f})', color='green', linestyle='--')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['lower_band'], label=f'-1 Std Dev ({std_dev:.2f})', color='red', linestyle='--')
    
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.title('What is the volatility of S&P 500 prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
